Hungary’s Karman Sees Budget Boost for Credit Ratings, WSJ Says

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-03-11T01:11:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/hungary-s-karman-sees-budget-boost-for-credit-ratings-wsj-says.html
Andras Karman, state secretary in  Hungary ’s  Economy Ministry , said he believes the government’s
new budget plans will raise the country’s slumping credit
ratings and reassure investors in the lead-up to a bond offering
planned for this year, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing
an interview.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
